<paragraph blockId="16.[110,649,527,1699]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Rhizome erect, stipes in whorls; rhizome scales narrowly lanceolate, light brown, sometimes with brown to black central stripe. Sterile lamina pinnatisect, with middle segments decurrent on rachis and lowest segments abruptly reduced to auricles; fertile lamina pinnate, with much reduced pinnae. Sori extending along most of fertile pinnae; indusium entire.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
